    </figure>
  </div>

  <p>The system consists of 3 steps needed for oil, water, and sludge processing at high capacity:</p>

  <ol>
    <li><strong>Pre-Straining Module</strong> - separates debris (i.e., rocks, debris, bolts, etc.) from the untreated waste oil.</li>
    <li><strong>Decanter Centrifuge Module</strong> - to de-sludge the pre-strained oil to separate the bulk of the sludge.</li>
    <li><strong>Vertical Disc Centrifuge Module</strong> - for oil-water separation and to remove small particles down to 1-micron level.</li>
  </ol>

